[Enter feedback here]
In the current limitation of Continuous backup mode, one is that "Azure Cosmos DB API for SQL or MongoDB accounts that create unique index after the container is created are not supported for continuous backup.". 

Here are two questions:

-  how to check whether the unique index is crated after the container is created for my Cosmos DB account?

- The doc about "[Define a unique key](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/unique-keys#define-a-unique-key)" shows "You can define unique keys only when you create an Azure Cosmos container.". From this doc, it seems that there is no chance to create unique index after the container is created. Does that mean we can remove this limitation?

[Enter feedback here]
In the wiki [Configure Azure Cosmos DB account with periodic backup](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/configure-periodic-backup-restore), it suggested that "If everything looks good, you can migrate the data back to the primary account. Although it is possible to use the restored account as your new active account, it's not a recommended option if you have production workloads.", i.e, migrate the restored data to the original Cosmos DB. 

**Is it same for Cosmos DB periodic backup mode?** 

In the "[Restore an Azure Cosmos DB account that uses continuous backup mode](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/cosmos-db/restore-account-continuous-backup)" wiki page, I can't find the answer.
